#13001
@@WNorth Wall Walk, West End@@N~
@@WThe battlement walkway stretches east along the @@Wnorth wall@@N of
@@BKiess@@W, broad enough for two sentries to pass without breaking stride.
Crenellations rise at regular intervals, each fitted with iron brackets
that once held crossbow rests. The city's rooflines spread below to the
south; to the north, open borderland rolls away into morning haze. The
stone underfoot is worn smooth by years of patrol boots. A faint smell of
lamp oil lingers from the brazier at the tower to the west.@@N
