#13003
@@WNorth Gate Customs Yard@@N~
@@WThe open-air customs area occupies a broad stretch of the @@Wnorth wall
walk@@N between the gate approach and the battlement corridor to the west.
Arriving caravans are directed here for manifest inspection before they
are cleared into the city proper. Clerks with portable writing desks work
from a covered awning along the inner parapet edge, checking inventory
declarations against posted tariff schedules. Chalk guide-lines on the
stone direct wagon teams into parallel lanes. The gate arch is visible
to the east; the wall walk continues west.@@N
