#13004
@@WNorth Gate Staging Yard@@N~
@@WThe staging yard is a broad cobbled expanse used to marshal arriving
wagons before they are cleared into the city. Painted lane markers on the
stone guide teams of oxen and horses into parallel queues. A water trough
runs along the north wall for animals; a second, smaller one nearby is
labeled for human use. Wagon wheel ruts are worn deep into the older
sections of cobblestone near the gate arch. The customs office sits to
the west; the gate arch itself opens to the north.@@N
