bearing the carved insignia of the Wall Command's founding charter.
A ladder shaft drops down into the guard post below. The city's east
market district is visible over the rooflines to the south. Sentries pass
through regularly; the footing is swept and maintained. An iron ring set
into the stonework once anchored a signal chain used to relay gate status
along the full north perimeter.@@N
