@@WNorth Wall Walk, East End@@N~
@@WThe battlement walkway reaches its east end here, the wall turning
south toward the northeast tower. The parapet on the north face is wider
than average, fitted with an old catapult platform now used as a watch
station. Wind off the borderlands carries the smell of pine and turned
earth. The city drops away to the south in an orderly descent of
rooftops and avenues. The wall's stonework shows older repairs in darker
stone patching the original white.@@N
