@@WNortheast Watchtower@@N~
@@WThe northeast watchtower commands a view across the open borderlands
to the north and the scholastic district of @@BKiess@@W below. The beacon
brazier here burns with a slightly different colored flame than the
northwest tower — local tradition holds that blue-tinged fire marks the
morning watch, white fire the evening. The carved statue of @@WThe Watcher
of Daybreak@@N faces east, hands cupped as if catching the first light.
Battle plaques here list the names of scouts who went east into the wastes
and did not return.@@N
