@@WWestern Wall Avenue, North@@N~
@@WThe inner avenue running along the base of the west wall is wide enough
for a laden cart but not two abreast. The wall face to the west is
dressed stone with narrow arrow slits at head height. Torch brackets
every ten paces keep the avenue lit at night. The Caravan Rest Yard opens
to the east; the wall walk stair is visible to the north. Foot traffic
here tends toward the practical: drovers, supply handlers, and wall
sentries moving between posts.@@N
