@@WCaravan Rest Yard@@N~
@@WA packed-earth yard with a series of wooden lean-tos along the north
side provides resting space for caravan crews waiting on customs
clearance. The lean-tos are open-fronted, with simple plank benches and
fire rings that show heavy recent use. A notice board between two of the
shelters lists current waiting times and yard rules. Several feed bags
and rope coils are stacked near the entrance. The steady noise of animals
and conversation fills the yard. The main customs approaches lie to the
north, the city interior to the south.@@N
