@@WArrival Provisioner@@N~
@@WA tightly packed supply room caters specifically to newly arrived
travelers who need to restock before moving deeper into the city or
onward along the road. Stacked crates and barrels crowd the walls, each
labeled with contents and price in clear chalk script. A helpful attendant
behind the main counter can package a basic travel kit in under a minute.
Trail rations, rope, bandages, and lamp oil are the staples here. The room
smells of dried meat and pine pitch.@@N
