@@WCentral Arrival Plaza@@N~
@@WA wide paved plaza just south of the gate serves as the primary
dispersal point for arriving travelers. Eight stone benches arranged in
a rough circle provide seating; a public water basin at the center runs
continuously from a pipe fed by the city's elevated cistern. Posted maps
on iron-framed boards show the city grid with service locations marked.
Greeters from the Temple of Concord and the Trade Syndics compete
politely for the attention of newcomers. The North Promenade continues
south; the gate arch is visible to the north.@@N
