@@WCourier Dispatch Hall@@N~
@@WA low interior hall with a high counter along the back wall operates
as the city's primary courier coordination point. Numbered cubbyholes
fill the wall behind the counter, most stuffed with rolled and sealed
messages. A dispatch board on the near wall shows current runner
assignments and expected delivery windows. Couriers in lightweight kit
move in and out with a brisk efficiency that leaves little room for
conversation. The smell of sealing wax and ink is persistent. An access
door to the west opens toward the arrival plaza.@@N
