@@WWagonwright's Yard@@N~
@@WA working livery stable and wagon repair yard shares space on the
avenue east of the north wall walk. The sound of hammering and the
smell of horse sweat define the place. Three wagons in various states
of repair fill the center of the yard; a fourth, freshly painted, waits
near the exit for its owner. A rack of spare wheel components lines
the east wall. The wagonwright herself supervises an apprentice fitting
an iron tire with practiced calm. Stalls at the back hold a half-dozen
horses for overnight boarding.@@N
