with a stone marker at the center, its four faces carved with compass
directions and district names. Merchants' carts pass through without
slowing, their drivers familiar with the right-of-way conventions that
keep the crossing from grinding to a halt. A pair of Kiess citizens
debate the price of imported spices near the marker. The noise level
here is consistent and energetic. All four cardinal streets open from
this point into their respective district sections.@@N
