@@WCivic Notice Square@@N~
@@WA small open plaza with a central waystone serves as the city's main
public announcement point. The waystone is a tall cut block with a
glass-covered face on each side, each face displaying current official
notices: taxation schedules, event announcements, and public law
reminders. Three smaller boards on posts nearby hold community postings
that the city clerk reviews weekly. A street sweeper works around the
base of the waystone with methodical patience. The square is a natural
gathering and loitering point; several citizens linger here at any
given time.@@N
