@@WApothecary Lane@@N~
@@WA street with a denser-than-usual concentration of herbalist and
potion-maker stalls gives this lane its name. Bundles of dried herbs
hang from the overhangs of several buildings, and the air carries a
complex layered smell that shifts with every few steps. A skilled
herbalist offers identification of found plant samples for a modest
fee. Bottles, pouches, and sealed clay jars crowd the display tables.
The competition between vendors is polite but constant. The scholastic
colonnade lies to the east; the notice square is to the west.@@N
