@@WSage's Alcove@@N~
@@WA quiet interior room functions as a lore consultation and historical
archive service. Bookshelves line every wall from floor to ceiling,
accessible by a rolling ladder on a brass rail. The resident sage sits
at a reading stand near the window, a magnifying lens perched on their
nose, annotating a marginal note in a text about pre-Evermeet settlement
patterns. Clients may hire research time by the hour; the rate is posted
on a small placard by the door. A dedicated section on the east wall
holds recent expedition reports from the Forest of Confusion scouts.@@N
