#13018
temple concord acolyte~
a Temple Concord acolyte~
@@WA Temple Concord acolyte@@N moves through the district on temple business.
~
@@WA Temple Concord acolyte@@W carries a small stack of votive tablets
bound in linen, apparently making deliveries or collections for the
temple. The junior compact insignia on the collar is slightly new and
still well-pressed. Acolytes at this level do most of the temple's
practical legwork — notice posting, shrine supply, and public
liaison — before taking on more formal pastoral duties.
~
