the Wall Command: heavier kit than a standard sentry, the sergeant's
chevron on the right shoulder, and the deliberate gait of someone
doing a patrol inspection rather than a guard post stint. She notes
everything in her sector and documents anything that deviates from
the expected pattern in a small field notebook.
