@@WA Prism Square orator@@W addresses a small knot of listeners from a
position near one of the prismatic waystones, delivering commentary on
city history, current trade conditions, or the founding compact with the
rehearsed fluency of someone who has given this particular address before.
The orator's tone is civic rather than political, informative rather
than inflammatory. Public speaking at the Prism plaza is a long
tradition in Kiess.
~
